<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>404 - Page Not Found</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            background-color: #f4f4f9;
            color: #333;
        }

        .container {
            text-align: center;
            max-width: 600px;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .error-code {
            font-size: 6rem;
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #ff6b6b;
            margin: 0;
        }

        .message {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            margin: 10px 0;
        }

        .description {
            font-size: 1rem;
            color: #555;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .home-link {
            display: inline-block;
            text-decoration: none;
            color: #fff;
            background-color: #007bff;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-size: 1rem;
            transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
        }

        .home-link:hover {
            background-color: #0056b3;
        }

        .illustration {
            max-width: 100%;
            height: auto;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="container">
        <p class="error-code">404</p>
        <p class="message">Oops! Page Not Found</p>
        <p class="description">The page you are looking for might have been removed, had its name changed, or is
            temporarily unavailable.</p>
        <a href="/dashboard" class="home-link">Go Back to Home</a>
        <img src="https://indexsy.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/What-is-404-error.jpg" alt="404 Illustration"
            class="illustration">
    </div>
</body>

</html>